This place was awesome for Caribbean food! We got the jerk chicken which was delicious! We also got the Caribbean meatballs which were flavorful and a little spicy! The plantains and rice were good too! We also had the peppered shrimp was great too! I did want to try the macaroni pie but unfortunately it was sold out.  Service was friendly and take out was a very easy process! The restaurant is small but looks like they may have a cute outdoor area when things are back to normal! They do have a parking lot which is a plus in Providence!

My girlfriend and I had a great dinner at the garden of eve Caribbean restaurant. We started with an accra appetizer, which we had never tried before. It was hot and crispy with a side of an oil based hot sauce. We also tried a Jamaican ginger beer. The chef/owner came around to our table, introduced herself, and recommended the snapper. What a great choice. We really enjoyed the fish with a side of rice and beans and fried plantains. One portion was big enough for two people. The chef/owner sat down with us after the meal and we chatted for quite a while. Even though she is a New England Patriots fan (go Bengals!), she is an awesome person who runs an awesome restaurant. Got to love family run, local businesses that care about their communities. We will be back!
